In this article, President Joe Biden speaks at an event honoring Speaker Nancy Pelosi. He thanks Pelosi for her leadership and describes her as one of the most consequential speakers in US history. Biden praises Pelosi for her ability to get bills passed and lists some of the legislation she has been involved in, including the rescue of the economy during the Great Depression, the Affordable Care Act, and the defense of democracy after the January 6th insurrection. He also acknowledges Pelosi's advocacy for women's rights, particularly the right to choose. Biden concludes by introducing Pelosi to speak at the event.